      <hedline>
        <hl1>Economic Adviser to Quit</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>WASHINGTON, July 27</dateline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lael Brainard, who serves as Pres Clinton's representative to Group of 8 industrial nations and helps set international economic policy for administration, plans to leave administration by end of summer (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Lael Brainard, who serves as President Clinton's representative to the Group of 8 industrial nations and helps set international economic policy for the administration, plans to leave the White House by the end of the summer.</p>
        <p>Ms. Brainard, 38, is the latest in a string of administration officials to leave their jobs as Mr. Clinton's presidency nears its end.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Lael Brainard, who serves as President Clinton's representative to the Group of 8 industrial nations and helps set international economic policy for the administration, plans to leave the White House by the end of the summer.</p>
        <p>Ms. Brainard, 38, is the latest in a string of administration officials to leave their jobs as Mr. Clinton's presidency nears its end.</p>
        <p>A former Massachusetts Institute of Technology economics professor, Ms. Brainard joined the administration in 1994 as a deputy to the National Economic Adviser Gene Sperling.</p>
      </block>
